{{Infobox academic | honorific_prefix = Prof. | name = Karen Bryan | honorific_suffix ={{post nominals|unlinked=FRCSLT}}, {{post nominals|UK|OBE}} | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | occupation = {{plainlist| * Speech Therapist }} | awards = | alma_mater = University of Newcastle | thesis_year = | discipline = | sub_discipline = | workplaces = {{plainlist| * University of Surrey * Sheffield Hallam University * University of Greenwich }} }}
'''Karen Bryan''' {{post nominals|unlinked=FRCSLT}} {{post nominals|UK|OBE}} is a [[speech therapist]], and a Professor and Deputy Vice-Chancellor (Academic) at the [[University of Greenwich]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gre.ac.uk/articles/archive/public-relations/welcome-professor-karen-bryan |title=Welcome to Professor Karen Bryan, Deputy Vice-Chancellor (Academic) |publisher=University of Greenwich |accessdate=12 October 2018}}</ref>
==Career== Bryan qualified as a speech and language therapist from the [[Newcastle University|University of Newcastle]] and also gained her PhD there. Her research interests are in workforce development and the effectiveness of interventions for communication disorders associated with stroke, dementia and other neurological conditions.
Bryan was Head of the School of Health and Social Care at the [[University of Surrey]] before moving, in 2013, to the position of Pro Vice-Chancellor for its Faculty of Health and Wellbeing at [[Sheffield Hallam University]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www4.shu.ac.uk/mediacentre/sheffield-hallam-appoints-new-pro-vice-chancellor?filter=People |title=Sheffield Hallam appoints new Pro-Vice Chancellor |publisher=Sheffield Hallam University |accessdate=12 October 2018}}</ref> She is currently the Deputy Vice-Chancellor (Academic) at the University of Greenwich and Chair of the [[University Schools Trust]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ust.london/358/university-of-greenwich |title=University of Greenwich: Professor Karen Bryan |publisher=University Schools Trust |accessdate=12 October 2018}}</ref> She is also a visiting professor in the Department of Neuropsychology at the [[University of Warsaw]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www4.shu.ac.uk/mediacentre/professor-karen-bryan |title=Professor Karen Bryan |publisher=Sheffield Hallam University |accessdate=12 October 2018}}</ref>
Bryan was elected a Fellow of the [[Royal College of Speech and Language Therapists]] in 2011,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rcslt.org/honours_roll_call_1945-2016 |title=RCSLT Honours Roll Call |publisher=Royal College of Speech and Language Therapists |accessdate=12 October 2018}}</ref> and awarded an OBE in the [[2018 New Year Honours]] for services to Higher Education.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/671148/NY18_Queens_List_-_Final_.pdf |title=New Year's Honours list 2018 |date=29 December 2017 |publisher=UK Government |accessdate=12 October 2018}}</ref>
