'''Seifollah Vahid Dastjerdi''' (1926–1999) was head of the [[Red Crescent Society of the Islamic Republic of Iran]].<ref>[http://islam-pure.de/imam/news/news1999/jun1999.htm#30.06.1999 condolences over the death of dr. seifollah vahid dastjerdi (16.6.1999)]</ref>

During political turmoil in [[Tehran]] following the [[1987 Iranian pilgrim riots]] in Saudi Arabia, Seifollah Vahid Dastjerdi appeared on television speaking for Iran Red Crescent. In an interview seen on NBC Evening News for August 18, 1987, he claimed women victims of the violence had been deliberately killed.<ref>[http://tvnews.vanderbilt.edu/program.pl?ID=557781 Iran / Mecca Riots Aftermath]</ref>

In 1997, he was closely involved with Red Crescent's relief activities following the [[1997 Ardabil earthquake|Ardabil earthquake]].<ref>[http://www.salamiran.org/Media/IRNA/970303.html Death toll of Ardebil quake reaches 600] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/19970626184713/http://www.salamiran.org/Media/IRNA/970303.html |date=1997-06-26 }}</ref>

He was the father of [[Marzieh Vahid-Dastjerdi]].<ref>[http://www.mehrnews.com/fa/NewsDetail.aspx?NewsID=930643 Marzieh Vahid Dastjerdi joins government as Minister of Health ]</ref>
